⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Don Ready
node GDS · GDS · ⟦Don Ready:GDS:a409c3⟧

WHO   — Don Ready — the closer who can't keep anything
WHAT  — The parable's center: a man so good at manufacturing desire that he's lost the ability to want, until a dying lot and Ivy teach him to stay.
WHERE — GDS · The Goods (2009)  Framework inputs: The Goods: Live Hard, Sell Hard (2009, dir. Neal Brennan, Gary Sanchez/Paramount Vantage); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film is, underneath, about the cost of the close — and Don is the cost made human.
HOW   — By blitzing the sale, falling for Ivy, facing the partner he got killed, and choosing to stop closing.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I can sell you anything. That's the problem — I've sold everything, kept nothing, and I'm finally tired of driving away.

